info: ` markdown` markdown is used to add body size content to your fastn pages.

The `markdown` component is already included inside
[`doc-site`](fifthtry.github.io/doc-site). If you are using `doc-site` then 
don't add typography as fastn dependency.

-- site-doc.header: How to use?

Add below code to your FASTN.ftd and Import `typography` into your `.ftd` file

-- cb.code:
lang: ftd

\-- fastn.dependency: fastn-community.github.io/typography

-- cb.code: 
lang: ftd

\-- import: fastn-community.github.io/typography as tf

\-- tf.markdown:

This is markdown text. You can add [link](https://fastn.com) and
add **bold**, *italic* etc styles to markdown text.

-- site-doc.header: Properties:

Markdown has only body property as its default. 

-- site-doc.component-property: `body`

Body property is used to add body content of markdown component. Markdown
body is using common font-size, line-height and font-weight.

